title: Ce.775
creator: Crabtree, Donald "Don" Crabtree
description: According to Gene Titmus, this piece is an example of establishing positive cones and then removing material to expose them. This technique can also be used to make a hole in the center of a flake. "Example of establishing cones and then removing a flake to expose them. Also this technique was used to obtain a flake with a hole in it. (GT) See associated memo."
subject: experimental artifacts; lithics
source: Donald E. Crabtree Lithic Comparative Collection
